In any case, back to the point of using the question mark, I've seen the top convex used to articulate facial expressions like eyebrows and mouths placed where the period is at the bottom. If you're crafty, you can make the vertical portion of the question mark somewhat nose-like, or use it to separate the face into distinct planes like the ridge of the nose and forehead on faces.
